# Refresh-time route default

**Every page refresh that resolves to the home / storefront route is
auto-redirected to `/wingman`** (the immersive Wingman landing page).
The storefront remains reachable by clicking the DJI brand link in
the header — it just isn't the demo's canonical entry point.

| Refresh URL | Lands on |
|---|---|
| `/nto-shiseido-sandbox/` | `/nto-shiseido-sandbox/wingman` (replaceState) |
| `/nto-shiseido-sandbox/wingman` | `/nto-shiseido-sandbox/wingman` (no change) |
| `/nto-shiseido-sandbox/wingman/plan?q=...` | `/nto-shiseido-sandbox/wingman/plan?q=...` (no change) |
| any product / PLP / category page | unchanged — only `/` is rerouted |

## Where this lives in code

The redirect happens once, inside the `useState` lazy initializer of
`PrototypeNavigationProvider` in `src/prototypeRoutes.tsx`:

```typescript
const initial = getRouteState(window.location.pathname, window.location.search);
if (initial.currentRoute === ROUTES.home) {
  const wingmanUrl = toBrowserPath(ROUTES.wingman);
  window.history.replaceState({}, "", wingmanUrl);
  return getRouteState(wingmanUrl, "");
}
return initial;
```

Two design decisions that aren't obvious from the code:

1. **`replaceState`, not `pushState`.** A pushState would put the
   bare `/` into the browser history stack, so hitting Back from
   `/wingman` would bounce the shopper to a route they never
   actually visited. `replaceState` swaps the URL in place — the
   shopper's history starts cleanly at `/wingman`.
2. **The redirect ONLY fires for `ROUTES.home`.** Any other
   resolved route (product detail, PLP, wingman plan, about, etc.)
   is left alone so deep links keep working.

## Sibling rule

The experience-switcher defaults (Concept = Immersive, Platform =
Desktop) live in `agent-mode-defaults.mdc`. Together they enforce
that **every fresh visit lands the shopper on the immersive Wingman
page in desktop mode**, regardless of what they did in a previous
session.

## Forbidden patterns

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — pushState pollutes history with the bare `/` the user never visited.
window.history.pushState({}, "", wingmanUrl);

// ❌ BAD — redirecting from inside an effect causes a visible flash of
//        the storefront before the redirect fires. The lazy useState
//        initializer runs synchronously before first paint.
useEffect(() => {
  if (currentRoute === ROUTES.home) navigate(ROUTES.wingman);
}, []);

// ✅ GOOD — replaceState in the lazy initializer, no flash, clean history.
const [routeState, setRouteState] = useState(() => {
  const initial = getRouteState(...);
  if (initial.currentRoute === ROUTES.home) {
    window.history.replaceState({}, "", toBrowserPath(ROUTES.wingman));
    return getRouteState(toBrowserPath(ROUTES.wingman), "");
  }
  return initial;
});
```

## When changing this rule

1. Update the conditional at the top of `PrototypeNavigationProvider`.
2. Update the table at the top of this file with any new exempt routes.
3. If the canonical entry point changes (e.g. from Wingman to a new
   landing page), update `agent-mode-defaults.mdc` too — both rules
   should describe the same first-impression experience.
